<br>
Servant of Ro<br>
This ability calls a loyal servant into being who will repeatedly hurl fire at your target. Each rank of this ability increases the amount of time that the servant is able to remain by your side (45, 70, and 90 seconds). You may train the ranks of this ability at or after levels 61, 63, and 65.<br>
<br>
Host of the Elements<br>
This ability calls an assault of elemental minions into existence directed at a target. The minions attack the target without question until they are called back to their plane 60 seconds later. The initial rank of this ability calls five elementals. Additional ranks add two elementals each. You may train the ranks of this ability at or after levels 63, 64, and 65.<br>
<br>
Feigned Minion<br>
This ability allows you to instruct your pet to feign death via the '/pet feign' command. Three ranks of this skill are available, causing your pet to succeed 25%, 50%, and 75% of the time, respectively. You gain the ability to train an additional rank at levels 61, 63, and 65.<br>
<br>
Hastened Banishment<br>
This ability decreases the amount of time required between uses of Turn Summoned by ten percent per rank. You may train in this ability once each level, upon reaching level 63.<br>
<br>
An unknown one: Elemental Translocation<br>
Mage ports perhaps?<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
and here's one that all casters will like:<br>
<br>
Advanced Spell Casting Mastery<br>
This ability increases the chance of making your specialization checks by five percent per rank. The effect reduces your chance to fizzle and increases your chance of using less mana when casting a spell. You may train in this ability once each level upon reaching levels 62, 63, and 64. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ukathodos.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kathodos</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 112<br> <font color=#333333>(9/24/02 10:51:34 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm46.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=28.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.battle.net/war3/images/human/units/animations/waterelement.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Planar Abilities revealed!</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://eq.crgaming.com/viewarticle.asp?Article=4779">EQ.CastersRealm.com -&gt; POP AA ABILITIES, SEPTEMBER 24, 2002</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<br>
No classes are associated with the list as yet, though many of them are pretty clearly one class or another.  The melee ones are harder to pick out, as they can't be cross referenced with Lucy and may apply to multiple melee classes.<br>
<br>
Many seem to be all about reducing the reuse time on existing Class AA abilities, 10% per level over 3 levels, max of 30%.  They are named as &quot;Hastened [Class AA Name]&quot;.  For example, Clerics get Hastened Resurrection, Hastened Divinity, while a Wizard would get Hastened Exodus, etc.<br>
<br>
How much of a differnce will these make to the AA reuse times?<br>
72 minute AA - 64.8 minutes first level, 57.6 minutes second, 50.4 minutes third.<br>
144 minute AA - 129.6 minutes first level, 115.2 minutes second, 100.8 minutes third.<br>
